translated: Gustav, school inspector, Trollhättan, b. 4/1/92 in Karlskoga. Married on 21 with Märta Hildegard Fallström. Children: Sylvia b. 22, Torild b. 24, Torbjörn b. 25. - Primary school diploma: graduated in Strängnäs 1916, Bachelor of Arts in Gothenburg 1920, studied in Vienna 1931. Teacher at Karlskoga folk high school 1916-1917, member of the Swedish Missionary Society 1919-1923, primary school teacher in Grängesberg 1923-1933, municipal school inspector in Trollhättan since 1934. Deputy chairman of the child welfare board, chief of evacuation, Arvid Håkan Herbert, civil engineer, Gothenburg, b. 3/2/01 in Gothenburg to engineer Carl W. and Charlotta Söderlind. Married on 27 with Elsa Cartlson. Children: Siv b. 27, Gun b. 29, Bo b. 34, Carl-Gustaf b. 41. - Passed high school exams in 1920, graduated from CTH in 1923. Engineer at Betong A-B West Sweden in Gothenburg. Among our country's top high divers with high, straight jumps as specialty ("Fågeln" - The Bird), first in straight jumps at the Olympic Games in Antwerp 1920, eighth in Paris 1924, second in Nordic Championships in Copenhagen 1925, Swedish champion in straight jumps in 1932, second in Swedish Championships in 1924, 1925, 1933, 1934, and 1936, third in 1931 and 1935, second in various jumps in 1925, 1934, and 1935, second in springboard diving in 1927, etc. Member of the Swimming Department 1902 in Gothenburg. Awarded the Swedish Swimming Federation honorary badge.
